<DocsPageTitle>
    Blazorise Sizes
</DocsPageTitle>

<DocsPageLead>
    Apply consistent size tokens to buttons, inputs, modals, and figures without custom CSS.
</DocsPageLead>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    Size enums provide a shared vocabulary for scaling UI elements across providers, so a small button or large modal feels consistent no matter which CSS framework you use.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    How it works
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    Use <Code>Size</Code> to scale components such as <Code Tag>Button</Code>, <Code Tag>TextInput</Code>, and <Code Tag>Badge</Code>.
    Use <Code>ModalSize</Code> for modals and <Code>FigureSize</Code> for figures when you need predictable, token-based sizing without custom CSS.
</DocsPageParagraph>

